  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Do testosterone gummies actually work?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'The effectiveness depends entirely on the specific ingredients and their doses. Several ingredients in testosterone gummies have clinical evidence for supporting testosterone levels: ashwagandha (KSM-66) increased testosterone by 17% in a 2019 study in the American Journal of Men\'s Health. Tongkat ali increased testosterone by 37% in a 2012 JISSN study. Fenugreek improved free testosterone by 46% in a 2020 Phytotherapy Research study. Zinc supplementation restores testosterone in zinc-deficient men. However, many testosterone gummies use underdosed proprietary blends or ingredients without clinical support. The key is choosing products with clinically studied ingredients at their researched doses.' } },
