    <h2 id="testosterone-decline">Understanding Natural Testosterone Decline and What Supplements Can Do</h2>

    <p>Testosterone is the primary male sex hormone, responsible for muscle mass maintenance, bone density, red blood cell production, fat distribution, libido, mood regulation, and cognitive function. Starting around age 30, testosterone production begins a gradual decline of approximately 1 to 2% per year — a process known as andropause. By age 50, many men have testosterone levels 20 to 30% below their peak. This decline is accelerated by chronic stress, poor sleep, excess body fat, nutrient deficiencies, sedentary lifestyle, and excessive alcohol consumption.</p>

