    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Testosterone Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Do testosterone gummies actually work?</summary><p>Effectiveness depends on specific ingredients at clinical doses. KSM-66 ashwagandha: +17% testosterone. Tongkat ali: +37%. Testofen fenugreek: +46% free testosterone. Zinc restores levels in deficient men. Many products use underdosed blends — choose products with clinically studied ingredients.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What causes low testosterone in men?</summary><p>Natural 1-2% annual decline after 30, accelerated by chronic stress, poor sleep, excess body fat, zinc/vitamin D deficiency, sedentary lifestyle, and alcohol consumption. Addressing these factors amplifies supplement effectiveness.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What are the best testosterone ingredients?</summary><p>KSM-66 ashwagandha (600mg), tongkat ali (200-400mg), Testofen fenugreek (600mg), zinc (30mg), vitamin D3 (3,000 IU), and D-aspartic acid (2,000-3,000mg) — all with published clinical evidence.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Are testosterone gummies safe?</summary><p>Herbal ingredients and micronutrients have demonstrated safety in trials up to 12 weeks. They do not carry TRT risks (shrinkage, infertility, polycythemia). Avoid with hormone-sensitive conditions or blood thinners. Regular bloodwork recommended.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How long do they take to work?</summary><p>Cortisol reduction: 2 weeks. Testosterone optimization: 8-12 weeks. Zinc/D restoration: 3-6 months. Plan a minimum 8-12 week trial with consistent daily dosing.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can testosterone gummies replace TRT?</summary><p>No. They support natural production — they cannot replicate TRT magnitude. For clinically diagnosed hypogonadism (below 300 ng/dL), prescription TRT is appropriate. Natural supplements target suboptimal but not deficient levels.</p></details>

